@startuml revised sequence

actor Caller
participant "Python wrapper" as Python
participant "KeyExchangeLibrary" as Cpp
participant "python-can Bus" as Bus
participant "Anchor" as Anchor

== configure ==

Caller -> Python : KeyExchangeService(anchor_idx, bus)
Python -> Cpp : KexCreate(anchor_idx)
Python -> Cpp : KexRegisterCanCallbacks(send_cb, recv_cb)
Python -> Cpp : KexSetFactoryPrivateKey(...)
Python -> Cpp : KexSetSecocKey(...)
Python -> Cpp : KexSetIv(...)

== run exchange ==

Caller -> Python : run()
Python -> Cpp : KexRun(timeout_ms)

loop internal C++ state machine
  Cpp -> Cpp : build UDS request for current step
  Cpp -> Python : send_cb(can_id, data, len)
  Python -> Bus : bus.send(can.Message(...))
  Bus -> Anchor : CAN FD request

  Anchor -> Bus : CAN FD response
  Cpp -> Python : recv_cb(buffer, max_len, timeout)
  Python -> Bus : bus.recv(timeout)
  Python --> Cpp : can_id + response bytes

  Cpp -> Cpp : validate response
  Cpp -> Cpp : generate signature / ECDH / AES as needed
end

Cpp --> Python : status COMPLETE or FAILED
Python --> Caller : result

@enduml